-- IK investment partners sells Minimax to Kirkbi and ICG 
-- By Alexander Huebner and Jonathan Gould
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 05:22AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, June 12 (Reuters) - IK Investment Partners has sold a majority stake in German fire extinguisher maker Minimax Viking to Danish family holding Kirkbi A/S and asset manager Intermediate Capital Group Plc <ICP.L>, IK said on Thursday.

IK did not reveal financial details of the transaction. Financial sources said separately the sale values Minimax at 1.37 billion euros ($1.9 billion).